e look at the social lives of Canadian artists during a time of great effervescence and creative possibility. Gabor Szilasi: The Art World in Montreal invites reflection on what has since been lost and gained. Brought to light over fifty years after they were taken, the images featured in this book reveal the centrality of one of Canada's leading photographers to the milieu he calls home.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aArtistsvPortraits. 7aART / Canadian.2bisacsh1 aLangford, Martha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSauvage, Suzanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSzilasi, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTousignant, Zoë, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978189561542540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781895615425423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781895615425/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles